    <note>Li(2) Zongyong [1101] Noted for fiscal expertise (xinji). According to Zhang(1) Fangping, Fang(3)'s [8075] son Zonge [3541] was an elder cousin, but Zongyong's father was Can(2) [17269] and his grandfather was Song(5) [17268], therefore second cousin at best. I am going to make Song(5) and Fang(3)'s father, Zhao(2) [17267], cousins, both descended from Zhaojun Li(2) Zuoche [17266]. I am also going to assume that Zongyong's grandfather was the first member of his branch of the lineage to move to Kaifeng with his kin Fang(3), therefore Fang(3) will be the identified migrant. Zongyong was Maozhi's [1061], Maoli's [3519] and Maoxian's [3518] father. Xue(1) Zhongru's [7108] father-in-law. Zhang Fangping, WJ, 39.22b; XCB, 119.5a, 120.11a, 134.1a, 140.7b; SHY:ZG, 64.42b; Yu Jing, WJ, 10.10a. CBD, 2, 988.</note>
